{
  "text": "was unmethylated in all 10 control BM samples. These results suggest that PCDH17 methylation is a specific phenomenon for ALL blasts at diagnosis. PCDH17 is a member of nonclustered protocadherin, a subfamily of cadherin superfamily genes. [CITATION_1] PCDH17 is frequently downregulated through promoter hypermethylation in a number of cancers. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] The restoration of PCDH17 expression reduces cell proliferation and migration in esophageal squamous cell carcinoma [CITATION_5] and induces tumor cell apoptosis and autophagy in gastric and colorectal cancers. [CITATION_6] However, there was no correlation between methylation status and mRNA expression level of PCDH17 in patients with BCP ALL in this study, implying the involvement of alternative mechanisms in the regulation of PCDH17 gene expression. Accordingly, the association of PCDH17 methylation with a poor prognosis may occur through a mechanism that is independent of methylation-mediated transcriptional silencing.",
